-- Anglo American May Buy Oppenheimer $3.1 Billion De Beers Stake, Times Says
-- B y   R a c h e l   G r a h a m
-- 2010-12-19T10:09:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-19/anglo-american-may-buy-oppenheimer-stake-in-de-beers-times-says.html
Anglo American Plc,  a miner of
platinum, palladium and nickel, may buy the Oppenheimer family
out of diamond company D e Beers , the Sunday Times reported,
citing unidentified sources.  The stake could cost at least 2 billion pounds ($3.11
billion), according to the report. The family owns 45 percent of
de Beers, the Sunday Times said.  “Anglo American wouldn’t want to comment on speculation or
rumours,” spokesman Pranill Ramchander said when contacted by
telephone in South Africa.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Rachel Graham  in London 
